        <section class="series-hero reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">3,200 Years. 138 Generations. One Question.</p>
          <h1>The Architecture of Survival</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            A 12-book epic exploring genetic memory, civilizational collapse, and the eternal
            conflict between knowledge preservation and genetic control. Neither side is evil.
            Both genuinely believe they're saving humanity. The moral ambiguity is the point.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- High-Level Concept -->
        <section class="concept-section reveal delay-1">
          <h2>The Core Concept</h2>
          <p>
            In 1177 BCE, during the Bronze Age Collapse, Egyptian scribe Nefertari makes a
            discovery that will echo through 3,200 years of human history: pattern recognition
            isn't just teachable—it's inheritable. Using Egyptian medical knowledge of bloodlines
            and genetic inheritance, she encodes collapse prediction methodology directly into DNA
            methylation patterns, creating humanity's first "genetic memory" system.
          </p>
          <p>
            But her colleague Amenhotep reaches the opposite conclusion. Civilizational collapse
            isn't preventable through distributed knowledge—it's inevitable due to systemic
            complexity. The only rational response is engineering optimal survivors through
            selective breeding programs that concentrate desirable traits across generations.
          </p>
          <p>
            Two competing networks emerge: the Genesis Protocol (defensive, egalitarian,
            knowledge-distribution focused) and the Order (offensive, hierarchical, genetic
            engineering focused). For the next 3,200 years, they will battle across every major
            historical period, embedding their methodologies in religious movements, scientific
            revolutions, political upheavals, and technological breakthroughs.
          </p>
          <p>
            The saga follows both networks' descendants as they discover the truth: they're
            Generation 90, or 138, or 48 in unbroken bloodlines stretching back to Bronze Age Egypt.
            The "memories" they experience aren't hallucinations—they're actual data transmitted
            through epigenetic markers, a biological hard drive carrying 3,000+ years of accumulated
            knowledge, trauma, and methodology.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Two Networks Comparison -->
        <section class="reveal delay-1">
          <div class="concept-section">
            <h2>The Two Networks</h2>
            <p>
              The fundamental philosophical divide that drives the entire saga. Both networks
              genuinely believe they're protecting humanity. Both have 3,200 years of evidence
              supporting their worldview. Neither is purely good or evil—the moral complexity
              is central to the narrative.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="networks-comparison">
            <div class="network-panel defensive reveal delay-2">
              <h3>The Genesis Protocol</h3>
              <span class="network-label">Defensive Network</span>
              <p>
                <strong>Founded:</strong> 1177 BCE by Nefertari<br />
                <strong>Philosophy:</strong> "Collapse is PREVENTABLE through pattern recognition."
              </p>
              <p>
                Collapse happens because people fail to recognize systemic patterns until too late.
                If you distribute pattern recognition methodology widely enough, populations can
                interrupt cascade failures before they become catastrophic.
              </p>
              <h4 style="margin-top: 20px;">Strategy</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Distribute knowledge as broadly as possible</li>
                <li>Embed methodology in culture, religion, art, science</li>
                <li>Teach pattern recognition to everyone, not just elites</li>
                <li>Make systems resilient through redundancy and diversity</li>
                <li>Trust human capacity for learning and adaptation</li>
              </ul>
              <h4 style="margin-top: 20px;">Historical Manifestations</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Early Christianity's egalitarian knowledge sharing</li>
                <li>Renaissance printing press revolution</li>
                <li>Enlightenment democratic philosophy</li>
                <li>Open-source software movements</li>
                <li>Internet knowledge distribution</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="network-panel offensive reveal delay-2">
              <h3>The Order</h3>
              <span class="network-label">Offensive Network</span>
              <p>
                <strong>Founded:</strong> 1177 BCE by Amenhotep<br />
                <strong>Philosophy:</strong> "Collapse is INEVITABLE—engineer who survives."
              </p>
              <p>
                Complexity breeds fragility. The more interconnected civilization becomes, the more
                vulnerable to cascade failure. You can't prevent collapse—you can only ensure the
                best genetic candidates survive to rebuild better.
              </p>
              <h4 style="margin-top: 20px;">Strategy</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Selective breeding programs to concentrate optimal traits</li>
                <li>Centralized knowledge control in elite bloodlines</li>
                <li>Engineer trauma resistance and cognitive superiority</li>
                <li>Observe collapses, recruit natural survivors</li>
                <li>Accept that most people can't handle complex knowledge</li>
              </ul>
              <h4 style="margin-top: 20px;">Historical Manifestations</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Medieval Church hierarchical control</li>
                <li>Renaissance patronage of select genius carriers</li>
                <li>Industrial era eugenics movements (corrupted version)</li>
                <li>Modern genetic engineering corporations</li>
                <li>Elite preservation bunker networks</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="concept-section reveal delay-2">
            <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--teal-dark); font-weight: 600; margin-top: 24px;">
