        <!-- The Seven Keys -->
        <section class="concept-section reveal delay-1">
          <h2>The Seven Keys</h2>
          <p>
            The Pattern Eye methodology developed by Nefertari in 1177 BCE. These seven layers of
            pattern recognition form the defensive network's core training system, embedded in
            culture through religion, philosophy, science, and art across 3,200 years.
          </p>

          <div class="keys-grid">
            <div class="key-card">
              <span class="key-number">1</span>
              <h4>Network Mapping</h4>
              <p>
                Identify all nodes and connections in a system. Who depends on whom? Which
                relationships are critical? Where are the concentration points?
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="key-card">
              <span class="key-number">2</span>
              <h4>Cascade Modeling</h4>
              <p>
                Trace how failure propagates. One node fails—what happens next? Second-order
                effects? Third-order? Where does it stop?
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="key-card">
              <span class="key-number">3</span>
              <h4>Threshold Detection</h4>
              <p>
                Systems appear stable until they're not. Find the tipping points where linear
                stresses trigger non-linear collapses.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="key-card">
              <span class="key-number">4</span>
              <h4>Feedback Loops</h4>
              <p>
                Positive feedback (accelerating spirals) vs. negative feedback (stabilizing forces).
                Which dominates? When do they flip?
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="key-card">
              <span class="key-number">5</span>
              <h4>Emergent Properties</h4>
              <p>
                The whole exhibits behaviors individual parts don't have. Recognize when system-level
