          <h2>The Collapse Pattern</h2>
          <p>
            Every major collapse in the saga follows the same underlying structure, regardless of
            historical period. This recursive pattern is what both networks fight over—can it be
            interrupted, or is it inevitable?
          </p>

          <h3>Stage 1: Optimization Trap</h3>
          <p>
            Systems optimize for efficiency, eliminating redundancy. Local improvements create
            global fragility. "Just-in-time" supply chains. Specialized knowledge. Centralized
            authorities. Everything works perfectly—until it doesn't.
          </p>

          <h3>Stage 2: Early Warning Signals</h3>
          <p>
            Small failures occur but are dismissed as isolated incidents. Pattern recognition
            specialists see connections, but authorities optimize for short-term stability. The
            defensive network attempts intervention. The Order observes who recognizes patterns
            naturally.
          </p>

          <h3>Stage 3: Cascade Initiation</h3>
          <p>
            A triggering event causes one critical node to fail. Could be plague, invasion, climate
            disaster, financial crash—the specific cause matters less than network structure. Other
            nodes that depended on it begin failing in sequence.
          </p>

          <h3>Stage 4: Positive Feedback Loop</h3>
          <p>
            Failures accelerate. Each collapse triggers more collapses. Refugees flee, spreading
            chaos. Trade networks sever. Food distribution breaks. Governments lose legitimacy.
            Violence spirals. The system enters positive feedback—self-reinforcing destruction.
          </p>

          <h3>Stage 5: Threshold Breach</h3>
          <p>
            The point of no return. Even if the triggering cause is resolved, the cascade continues
            under its own momentum. Recovery is no longer possible—only survival and eventual
            rebuilding.
          </p>

          <h3>Stage 6: Collapse & Selection</h3>
          <p>
            Massive population death. Knowledge loss. Infrastructure destruction. The Order's
            prepared bloodlines retreat to safe zones. Defensive network carriers attempt to
            preserve knowledge through the chaos. Natural selection operates at civilization scale.
          </p>

          <h3>Stage 7: Rebuild & Reset</h3>
          <p>
            Survivors rebuild, usually at lower complexity. The Order selectively breeds the best
            candidates. The defensive network re-embeds methodology in new cultural forms. The
            cycle begins again, 200-500 years later.
          </p>

